news.title: Thailand government to introduce property measures for low-income earners
news.para: Those measures include support for buying homes worth up to 1.5 million baht ($41,934.58), Krisada Chinavicharana said, adding that the government will also accelerate public investment spending.

news.title: Delhi civic body razes 131 buildings, seals 35 complexes in February
news.para: “The demolition has mainly targeted agricultural or vacant land where illegal plots or colonies were raised, attracting ignorant citizens to buy plots at cheaper rates. The actions are meant to spread a message among unscrupulous builders to abide by the Delhi Municipal Corporation Act.

news.title: Skyrocketing prices of sand deal a blow to construction work in Hyderabad
news.para: One of the essential materials for the realty sector, the fine sand which used to be available for ₹1,200 to ₹1,600 per tonne now costs ₹2,200 to ₹2,500 per tonne depending on the grade. With this, the cost of the sand per tipper lorry, which carries nearly 25 tonnes, has increased from around ₹35,000 to ₹55,000-₹60,000.

news.title: Germany's PBB tries to reassure on liquidity as shares drop
news.para: PBB, listed on the small-cap SDAX index, is heavily focused on the real estate industry, and its update on Thursday was the second unscheduled announcement in two days as its shares and bonds come under pressure. On Wednesday it described the U.S. market as "the greatest real estate crisis since the financial crisis".

news.title: Jharkhand CM to distribute first installment of Abua Awas Yojana on Friday
news.para: In the first phase, the CM will hand over 24,827 letters of acceptance in Kolhan division comprising 8,138 families from East Singhbhum district, West Singhbhum (10,252) and Seraikela-Kharswan district (6,437) along with the first installment of Rs 30,000 each, which will be transferred to their bank accounts through DBT.

news.title: Shivalik Group receives Sebi approval for AIF
news.para: The proposed AIF aims to raise up to Rs 300 crore through private placement, including Rs 150 Crore Green Shoe Option exercisable at the discretion of the investment manager.

news.title: West Bengal: Stamp duty sop for property transfer through gift deeds
news.para: In order to provide relief in property transfers within the family, I am happy to propose a maximum stamp duty of Rs 1,000 only in case of transfer of property by way of gift within the family,” minister of state for finance Chandrima Bhattacharya said.

news.title: Delhi HC hints at CBI probe into illegal construction
news.para: A bench of acting Chief Justice Manmohan and Justice Manmeet PS Arora also hinted at ordering a CBI probe to investigate lapses by all authorities in stopping unauthorised construction near centrally-protected monuments Nizamuddin ki Baoli and Barakhamba Tomb.

news.title: No LTCG tax if property redeveloped within three years: Experts
news.para: Experts said that societies should ensure there is a clause in the agreement with the builder that the project is completed within three years. A period longer than three years could attract long-term capital gain tax demand by the income tax department.

news.title: Gujarat RERA sets February 21 as new QPR deadline
news.para: Sources said that nearly 70% of the developers have completed the migration process and the issues pertaining to the new portal will be sorted out soon.

news.title: Town planner steps up heat on illegal colonies in Gurugram
news.para: Two illegal colonies, which were carved out on over 12 acres without the approval of competent authorities and in violation of Haryana Urban Development Act, 1975, were demolished in IMT Manesar on Thursday in presence of police personnel.

news.title: Grasim Industries' profit dips 41.5% to Rs 2,603.43 crore in Q3 FY24
news.para: The company had posted a net profit of Rs 4,454.59 crore during the October-December quarter a year ago, Grasim Industries said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: West Bengal government plans to revisit urban land ceiling act
news.para: Unveiling the 2024-25 budget, Minister of State (independent charge) for Finance Chandrima Bhattacharya announced that the state would "revisit and examine" the applicability of the Urban Land Ceiling Act and Land Ceiling provisions under the West Bengal Land Reforms Act."

news.title: Punjab RERA chairman resigns
news.para: Satya Gopal, a former additional chief secretary of Delhi, was considered close to Delhi CM Arvind Kejriwal and was appointed as the Rera chairman by AAP govt in Punjab in December 2022, following his retirement in July that year.

news.title: Property tax defaulters in Bengaluru hope for one-time settlement
news.para: Pointing at the impasse that lakhs of property holders find themselves in by defaulting in tax payments, several MLAs and MLCs from Bengaluru have demanded that the issue be resolved atthe earliest. A high-level meeting of Bengaluru’s legislators and ministers, convened by deputy chief minister DK Shivakumar a fortnight ago in Vikasa Soudha, also resolved to address the issue as early as possible.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body to hold another plots auction
news.para: The civic body announced that these plots will have a cumulative reserve price of Rs. 647.62 crore. The five plots on the block are in Vatva, Thaltej, Bodakdev and Vastral. The plots in Thaltej and Vatva are zoned for residential purposes while the other three are for commercial purposes in Bodakdev and Vastral.

news.title: Meghalaya CM proposes Rs 2,500 crore budget for new administrative city
news.para: He said the planned administrative city is coming up soon in Mawdiangdiang, about 12 km from city centre. It is a project that is going to be worth more than Rs 2500 crore if you were to include everything from road connectivity, water supply and infrastructure," he said addressing a meeting here.

news.title: JK Lakshmi Cement's net profit up 93.94% in Q3 FY24
news.para: JK Lakshmi Cement's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,719.54 crore in Q3 FY24, a growth of 9.10 per cent from Rs 1,576.06 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: The Ramco Cements' net profit increases by 59.48% in Q3 FY24
news.para: The Ramco Cements' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 2,117.39 crore in Q3 FY24, a growth of 4.80 per cent from Rs 2,020.37 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Pune civic body razes 29 properties illegally constructed on hilltop in Bibvewadi
news.para: A Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) official said these properties were built near Aai Mata Mandir and Shatrunjay Mandir areas.The administration had given notices to the occupants of these properties, comprising showrooms, godowns and shops.
